{"title":"Rogue Panda Blue Ridge Handlebar Harness","link":"https://theradavist.com/rogue-panda-blue-ridge-handlebar-harness/","date":1710854530000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-harness.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-harness.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-harness.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-harness.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-harness.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Flagstaff, Arizona’s Rogue Panda, just announced a sub 9 oz bar-mounted cradle for dry bags called the <a href=\"https://roguepanda.com/products/blue-ridge-handlebar-harness\" target=\"_blank\">Blue Ridge Handlebar Harness</a> ($185); let’s check it out!<br />\n<span></span></p>\n<p>The Blue Ridge is Rogue Panda’s most stable handlebar harness yet. It features two burly CNC-machined aluminum clamps made in Flagstaff, which hold your dry bag securely in place without the need for a head tube attachment.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1999\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-8.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-8.jpg?w=1999&amp;quality=75 1999w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-8.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-8.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-8.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"887\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-7.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-7.jpg?w=887&amp;quality=75 887w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-7.jpg?resize=768,1154&amp;quality=75 768w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2003\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-6.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-6.jpg?w=2003&amp;quality=75 2003w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-6.jpg?resize=1200,799&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-6.jpg?resize=2000,1331&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-6.jpg?resize=768,511&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/2024_Sedona_MTB_Fest-6.jpg?resize=1536,1022&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Seen in our <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2024-sedona-mountain-bike-festival-gallery/\" target=\"_blank\">Sedona Mountain Bike Festival</a> coverage this year!</em></p>\n<p>Twin carbon fiber bars hold your load away from your head tube, and nylon shims protect your handlebar (available in 35mm, 31.8mm, and 22.2mm sizes). The end result is a handlebar harness that just. won’t. move.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1336\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-lightweight.jpg?fit=1200,1336&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-lightweight.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-lightweight.jpg?resize=1200,802&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-lightweight.jpg?resize=768,513&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/blue-ridge-lightweight.jpg?resize=1536,1026&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lightweight aluminum and carbon fiber construction 9 oz</li>\n<li>Fits 22.2, 31.8, and 35mm handlebars</li>\n<li>No head tube attachment!</li>\n<li>Straps are attached to the harness for less fiddling</li>\n<li>Holds weight close to the handlebar for minimum flex</li>\n<li>Available with locking plastic buckles or USA-made Austere Mfg Cam Buckles</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://roguepanda.com/products/blue-ridge-handlebar-harness\" target=\"_blank\">Rogue Panda</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/rogue-panda-blue-ridge-handlebar-harness/\">Rogue Panda Blue Ridge Handlebar Harness</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"a13e999099168bc80f7a7a285819dc07b21aeeeb4d65019ea0670bd07f85ab18","category":"Cycling"}